 colour hues as well as the rhythm of the editing         process. Compare Serpico to The Conversation. You can see there's far         more edits in Lumet's classic compared to the more gentle slower pace         of Coppola's Conversation. This is also down to the editing style of Walter         Murch who prefers to only make cuts when absolutely necessary. Have a         look through the eight movies and make your own mind up.</p>      <p>Created by <a href="http://www.brendandawes.com/">Brendan Dawes</a></p></td>    <td align="left" valign="top"><img src="images/vertigo.jpg" /></td>    <td valign="top"><img src="images/frenchconnection.jpg" /></td>    <td align="left" valign="top"><img src="images/deliverance.jpg" /></td>    <td valign="top"><img src="images/serpico.jpg" /></td>    <td valign="top"><img src="images/theconversation.jpg" /></td>    <td valign="top"><img src="images/taxidriver.jpg" /></td>    <td valign="top"><img src="images/manwhowasntthere.jpg" /></td>    <td valign="top"><img src="images/roadtoperdition.jpg" /></td>  </tr></table></body></html>